quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
31,20,"Have you not seen that Allah has subjected to your service all that is in the heavens {1} and on the earth and has abundantly bestowed upon you all His bounties, both visible and invisible? {2} Yet some persons dispute regarding Allah {3} without having any knowledge or guidance or any illuminating Book. {4}",footnotes:1:“Apparent favors” imply those favors which are perceived by man in one way or the other
31,21,"When they are told: “Follow what Allah has revealed,” they say: “We will rather follow that which we have found our forefathers following.” (Will they follow that) even though Satan might invite them to the chastisement of the Blazing Fire? {1}",footnotes:1:“Whoever surrenders his face to Allah”: Who submits himself wholly to the service of Allah
31,22,"Whoever surrenders himself to Allah {1} and lives righteously {2} grasps the most firm handle. {3} The ultimate decision of all matters rests with Allah.",footnotes:1:That is
31,23,"So let the unbelief of the unbeliever not grieve you. {1} To Us is their return and then We shall inform them of all that they did. Surely Allah knows well even the secrets that are hidden in the breasts (of people).",footnotes:1:That is
31,24,"We allow them to enjoy themselves a while in the world and then We shall drive them in utter helplessness to a harsh chastisement."
31,25,"If you were to ask them: “Who created the heavens and the earth?” they will certainly reply: “Allah.” Say: “All praise and thanks be to Allah.” {1} Yet most of them do not know. {2}",footnotes:1:That
31,26,"All that is in the heavens and the earth belongs to Allah. {1} Verily He is All-Sufficient, Immensely Praiseworthy. {2}",footnotes:1:This has been explained in (E. N. 19 )above.|180296:“Words of Allah”: Allah’s creative works and the manifestations of His power and wisdom. This very theme has been presented in Surah Al-Kahf: Ayat 109 a little differently. A person might think there is exaggeration in this
31,27,"If all the trees on earth become pens, and the sea replenished by seven more seas were to supply them with ink, the Words of Allah would not be exhausted. {1} Verily Allah is Most Mighty, Most Wise.",footnotes:1:That is
31,28,"To create all of you or to resurrect all of you is to Him like (creating or resurrecting) a single person. Verily Allah is All-Hearing, All-Seeing. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
